The paper discusses the relevance of intensionality to logic and computer science, and proposes a categorical theory of intensionality. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a new P-categorical construct and discusses its theory, which could also place it in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also draws inspiration from the categorical semantics of modal logic, which could suggest a connection to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper's focus on algebraic formulations and logical devices could also place it in the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category. Finally, the paper's discussion of intensional devices and their abstraction could suggest a connection to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
